subSections.text:
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructed Old Chinese pronunciation *''hjeŋh'' or *''lheŋh'': 
* If the former case, then formally derived from {{och-l|聲|tr=*hjeŋ}} "sound";
* If the latter case, this word is related to {{och-l|聽|tr=*lhêŋ}} "to hear, to listen" (Boltz, 1994) and literally means "be renowned, someone who is renowned for his wisdom".
